# CGEM IDE key bindings
# Format: <action> <key>
#
# Supported keys: F1-F12, Ctrl+Letter
# (Ctrl+Shift, Shift+Alt and similar combos are not supported — unreliable in
# terminals and the Windows console, same reason vi/nano stick to simpler keys.)
#
# Top level: F1 = help, F2-F6 = open menu bars (File / Edit / Build / Options / Help).
# Menu items and editor actions: Ctrl+letter only (see layout below).
# Theme and Save As have no default shortcut.
#
# Ctrl+letter layout (one action per letter):
#   A select-all   B generate*   C copy        D goto definition
#   E free         F find        G goto line   H free
#   I (tab)        J free        K format      L (shell clear screen)
#   M (enter)      N find next   O open        P rename
#   Q quit         R free        S save        T free
#   U paste fmt    V paste       W free        X cut
#   Y redo         Z undo
# * Ctrl+B is Generate for now; action.build (compile) will reuse it later.

menu.file F2
menu.edit F3
menu.build F4
menu.options F5
menu.help F6

action.open Ctrl+O
action.save Ctrl+S
action.generate Ctrl+B
action.quit Ctrl+Q
action.copy Ctrl+C
action.cut Ctrl+X
action.paste Ctrl+V
action.paste_formatted Ctrl+U
action.select_all Ctrl+A
action.undo Ctrl+Z
action.redo Ctrl+Y
action.find Ctrl+F
action.find_next Ctrl+N
action.goto_line Ctrl+G
action.goto_definition Ctrl+D
action.rename Ctrl+P
action.format Ctrl+K
action.help F1

# Fixed editor keys (not remappable — terminal Tab / Shift+Tab):
#   Tab         increase nesting (4 spaces) or accept keyword hint
#   Shift+Tab   decrease nesting (4 spaces)
